==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weather-fend
<hw>Weath"er-fend`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To defend
from the weather; to shelter.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[We] barked the white spruce to <qex>weather-fend</qex> the
roof.</q> <rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weatherglass</ent>⟦br⟧
